mcs_matrix = np.zeros((n, n))
for i in range(n):
    print(molecules[i].GetNumAtoms())
    for j in range(i, n):
        if i == j:
            mcs_matrix[i, j] = 1
        else:
            mcs = rdFMCS.FindMCS([molecules[i], molecules[j]])
            # If MCS is found, get the number of common atoms
            if mcs.numAtoms:
                common_mol = Chem.MolFromSmarts(mcs.smartsString)
                num_common_atoms = common_mol.GetNumAtoms() if common_mol else 0
                min_atoms = min(molecules[i].GetNumAtoms(), molecules[j].GetNumAtoms())
                similarity = num_common_atoms / min_atoms if min_atoms > 0 else 0
                mcs_matrix[i, j] = similarity
                mcs_matrix[j, i] = similarity
            else:
                mcs_matrix[i, j] = 0
                mcs_matrix[j, i] = 0
    # Plot similarity matrix
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 10))

#Create distance matrix using similarity matrix
distance_matrix = np.zeros((n, n))
for i in range(n):
    print(molecules[i].GetNumAtoms())
    for j in range(i, n):
        if i == j:
            distance_matrix[i, j] = 0
        else:
            mcs = rdFMCS.FindMCS([molecules[i], molecules[j]])
            # If MCS is found, get the number of common atoms
            if mcs.numAtoms:
                common_mol = Chem.MolFromSmarts(mcs.smartsString)
                num_common_atoms = common_mol.GetNumAtoms() if common_mol else 0
                min_atoms = min(molecules[i].GetNumAtoms(), molecules[j].GetNumAtoms())
                similarity = num_common_atoms / min_atoms if min_atoms > 0 else 0
                distance_matrix[i, j] = 1- similarity
                distance_matrix[j, i] = 1- similarity
            else:
                distance_matrix[i, j] = 0
                distance_matrix[j, i] = 0
plt.figure(figsize = (10, 10))
sns.heatmap(distance_matrix, annot = True, cmap = "Reds", xticklabels = ligand_smiles, yticklabels = ligand_smiles)
plt.title("MCS Distance Matrix")
print(distance_matrix[1,17])
# Hierarchical Clustering using Murtagh clustering (WARDS)
linkage_matrix = sch.linkage(distance_matrix, method = "average")

# Dendrogram
plt.figure(figsize = (10, 10))
sch.dendrogram(linkage_matrix, labels = ligand_smiles, leaf_rotation = 90, leaf_font_size = 10)
plt.title("Hierarchical Clustering Dendrogram")
plt.xlabel("Ligands")
plt.ylabel("Distance")
plt.show()

# Group molecules by cluster
clusters = fcluster(linkage_matrix, t = 0.4, criterion = "distance")
cluster_dict = {}
for idx, cluster_id in enumerate(clusters):
    if cluster_id not in cluster_dict:
        cluster_dict[cluster_id] = []
    cluster_dict[cluster_id].append(ligand_smiles[idx])

# Draw molecules in each cluster
for cluster_id, cluster_smiles in cluster_dict.items():
    print(f"Cluster {cluster_id}")
    molecules = [Chem.MolFromSmiles(smiles) for smiles in cluster_smiles]
    img = Draw.MolsToGridImage(molecules, molsPerRow = 5, subImgSize = (200, 200))
    display(cluster_id, cluster_smiles, img)

# Compute intra-cluster and inter-cluster distances
intra_cluster_distances = []
inter_cluster_distances = []

for (i, j) in itertools.combinations(range(len(clusters)), 2):
    distance = distance_matrix[i, j]
    cluster_i = clusters[i]
    cluster_j = clusters[j]

    if cluster_i == cluster_j:
        intra_cluster_distances.append(distance)
    else:
        inter_cluster_distances.append(distance)

# Plot histograms for pairwise distances
plt.figure(figsize = (10, 10))

plt.subplot(2, 2, 1)
plt.hist(intra_cluster_distances, bins = 25, color = 'green', alpha = 0.7, label = 'Intra-cluster')
plt.title('Intra-cluster Distances')
plt.xlabel('Distance')
plt.ylabel('Frequency')

plt.subplot(2, 2, 2)
plt.hist(inter_cluster_distances, bins = 25, color = 'red', alpha = 0.7, label = 'Inter-cluster')
plt.title('Inter-cluster Distances')
plt.xlabel('Distance')
plt.ylabel('Frequency')

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

cluster_representatives = {}
for cluster_id, smiles_list in cluster_dict.items():
    affinities = [(smi, affinity_data[smi]) for smi in smiles_list if smi in affinity_data]
    # top representative (lowest Kd)
    representative = min(affinities, key=lambda x: x[1])
    cluster_representatives[cluster_id] = representative
    print(f"Target Name: Cyclin-dependent kinase 2")
    print(f"\nCluster {cluster_id}")
    print(f"Number of molecules in cluster: ", len(smiles_list))
    print("SMILES in cluster:")
    for smi, aff in affinities:
        print(f"  {smi}, Affinity: {aff} nM")
    # Visualize molecules
    mols = [Chem.MolFromSmiles(smi) for smi, _ in affinities]
    img = Draw.MolsToGridImage(mols, molsPerRow=5, subImgSize=(200, 200))

    # Plot histogram of affinities
